The paper proposes using answer-set programming (ASP) to declaratively describe complex data objects in object-oriented programming languages. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to the areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of ASP for generating objects subject to application-specific constraints, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper mentions the use of ASP solver technology, which could also be relevant to databases (cs.DB).
